Ordered online for pick-up about a month ago and portions were slightly smaller than usual. Tried again today and the portions were ridiculously small. Not only is this frustrating (getting charged the regular price for half the amount of food), but it's dangerous. My bf is diabetic and took insulin based on the number of carbs in the online nutrition calculator, but now, since we only received about half the regular food, he doesn't know how many carbs are actually in it and has to guess how many extra carbs to eat so he doesn't go low. Overcharging is one thing, but potentially putting someone in a coma because you can't give a portion that's in line with the company's posted nutritional information is unacceptable. Have never had this problem at any other location, so it's got to be a management problem here.
